title: Dan Osborne and Jacqueline Jossa 'to marry in Gary Barlow's £7 Million Cheshire mansion'
text:
Dan Osborne and Jacqueline Jossa 'to marry in Gary Barlow's £7 Million Cheshire mansion' The couple, who have a two year-old daughter, are set to tie the knot in Cheshire Share Get celebs updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
He may have rose to fame on TV series The Only Way Is Essex, but Dan Osborn e is planning to marry his partner in Cheshire. 
According to a report in The Sun , the hunky reality star will tie the knot with his actress girlfriend Jacqueline Jossa at Delamere Manor in Cheshire - which was once owned by Gary Barlow, no less. 
The loved-up couple, who have a two-year-old daughter, Ella, are planning a lavish bash for friends and family up north after falling in love with the posh property. 
But, given that Barlow sold the property in 2006 for a whopping £7 million, it won't be cheap. Dan Osbourne and Jacqueline Jossa are set to marry in July (Photo: Barcroft Media) Read More Dan Osborne posts cute birthday wishes on Instagram as Ella, his daughter with Jacqueline Jossa, turns two 
A source told the paper: “Jacqueline and Dan have been looking for a wedding venue for a while but nothing had really caught their eye. 
“Then when they saw Delamere Manor they fell in love with it. Like any couple, they want their big day to be perfect, even if it does mean their entire families travelling from their homes in London to Cheshire. 
“They are convinced that going the extra distance will be worth it and they have booked a date in July.” 
The venue's website describes itself as 'the most exclusive Manor House wedding venue in Cheshire'. (Photo: Barcroft Media) (Photo: Barcroft Media) Barlow sold the property for a staggering £7 million in 2006, which is when it became a wedding venue (Photo: Barcroft Media) Read More Jacqueline Jossa shares unseen proposal throwback as she gears up for wedding to Dan Osborne 
It adds: 'Overlooking a stunning six-acre lake and set amongst rolling Cheshire countryside, this breathtaking venue, provides complete privacy, outstanding service and luxurious accommodation.' 
The former residence of the powerful Wilbraham family, it has six master bedrooms, private dining rooms, picture perfect gardens, a Victorian pump house and its own music rooms, where Barlow wrote some of his biggest hits. 
Last year, Jacqueline and Dan were forced to postpone their original wedding plans after failing to find a suitable venue for their nuptials. 
Speaking to OK Magazine at the time, she said: "We just ran out of time to plan everything. I thought we had ages to get stuff sorted, then all of a sudden it was March and we didn’t have anything booked. We’ve not found a venue that’s perfect for us yet," said the actress. 
"We want to wait and find somewhere that we love." 
The Mirror have contacted representatives for both parties but are yet to receive a response. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
